title: Differential Cross Sections of the 39,41K(n,n`gamma) Reaction

x4freetext: Neutrons were produced via the T(p,n) 3He
reaction in a 3-cm-long gas cell operated at 1.2 atm.
The gamma-ray detector was a heavily
consisting of a central NaI(T1) crystal 6 cm in
diameter and 16.5 cm long surrounded by an annular
NaI(T1) crystal with a 21.5 cm outside diameter and
30.5 cm long. Additional data were taken at a neutron
energy of 3.42 MeV with a 6-cc Ge(Li) detector at 90
The sample was a 5.8-cm-diam sphere of KOH and was
located 8.7 cm from the gas cell along the beam axis.
- Corrections due to geometry: Corrections were
made for three additional geometrical effects. For
each of these the effect was calculated by an
- The effect of sample absorption of gamma rays and of
incident neutrons was calculated by numerical
integration of neutron and gamma-ray transmission
